<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="49" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="49">
It is expected this species would be found to be widely distributed in and around China. Identification is based on the comparison of the image of holotype (
<bibRefCitation author="Roux, P" journalOrPublisher="Roux, France" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" refId="B24" refString="Roux, P, Lassalle, B, Dubault, G, 2016. Les Trigonotomi. Revision. B. Lassalle et P. Roux, France" title="Les Trigonotomi. Revision. B. Lassalle et P." year="2016">Roux et al., 2016</bibRefCitation>
) and specimens from Andhra Prad., India. Compared with the specimens from India, 
<taxonomicName genus="T." lsidName="T. indica" pageId="0" pageNumber="49" rank="species" species="indica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="49">T. indica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Mêdog">Medog</normalizedToken>
is slightly larger and more vividly green on its pronotum.
</paragraph>
